Description:
The Digital Literacy Guide poster gives an illustrated breakdown of the skills that are necessary for navigating today's digital world. The poster has a blue/beige theme and has illustrations to help users understand what digital literacy is; how to use technology effectively, how to communicate online, and how to evaluate information. It identifies the key skills that students should have; how to conduct online research, critical thinking, and using digital tools ethically. The Digital Literacy Guide also outlines safe internet practices including; safeguarding your personal information, and recognisng the risks when interacting on the internet. At the end of the Digital Literacy Guide is a list of key takeaways that promote user awareness, ethical behaviour and responsible digital communication.
